/public/docs/wizard/questob
-------------------
 
Hmmm...So you want to know how to make a generic quest object, eh?  Well,
this is going to be one of the harder undertakings of your career here on
Darkwind.  As a matter of fact, I think that it'll probably be harder than
coding your quest, even.  Yeah, I'm pretty sure of that part.
 
--------------------
 
The first few lines in any quest object should be:
 
#include <mudlib.h>
#include <darkwind.h>
#define DESTINATION WIZROOMS+"quest_ro"
inherit GEN_QUEST;
 
  The define is the pathname of the quest room underneath the
  adventurer's guild.  When you have your quest approved and
  ready to be put in the game, tell an Imp+ to have it added
  to the mud's autoload file, and this will take care of moving
  it there automatically when the mud reboots.
  The inherit line sets up the object to be a quest object and will
  allow calls to the quest master object as defined below.
 
--------------------
 
set_name("name");
 
  string name.  Supply the quest object a name.
 
set_hint("hint");
  string hint.  This is what is printed out when a player does a
  "list <quest-name>" in the Adventurer's Guild.
 
--------------------
 
Wow.  Pretty darn hard, eh?
 
I'll supply you with an example, just in case you didn't get it from what's
been in the doc so far:
Oh, another good idea is to include a long detailed comment giving
specifics on how to solve your quest.  Then if some wiz needs to
know, the pathname of this file can be found from the object in
the quest room and the file looked at.
 
--------------------
 
#include <mudlib.h>
#include <darkwind.h>
#define DESTINATION WIZROOMS+"quest_ro"
inherit GEN_QUEST;
 
void reset(int iArg) {
// NOTE: There is no ::reset(iArg); because the quest master object doesn't
// have a reset() function.
  if (iArg)
    return;
  set_name("Pharaohs Curse");
  set_hint("\
Rid Egypt of the Curse of the Pharaoh.\n\
A medium level quest - takes more brains than brawn.\n");
  move_object(this_object(),DESTINATION);
// this line moves it to the quest room when the object is reset,
// which should happen when the mud reboots if this file is in
// the mud's autoload file
}
 
